description: Rehabilitation of the National Dispatch Centre in Baghdad, Iraq-Stage II

subproject.corporate outcome: Livelihoods and economic recovery generated, including infrastructure restoration, employment and sustainable income earning opportunities for crisis affected communities
subproject.description: To respond to immediate humanitarian need for electricity supply to essential services through the rehabilitation of the National Dispatch Centre and installation of associated remote terminal units for remote control facilities in nineteen (19) major power generation plants to improve the ability of the Ministry of Electricity to manage the electrical network of Iraq and operate under safe and reliable conditions
subproject.gender code: No noticeable contribution to gender equality
